================================================================================
THE PIPELINES ARE nf-core's WORK (the most important part)
================================================================================
The bioinformatics pipelines are the core of nf-claw, and they are authored by
the nf-core community (https://nf-co.re) — NOT by nf-claw. They are included
UNMODIFIED as pinned git submodules under pipelines/<name>/upstream/. Each
pipeline keeps its own authors, license and citation; see that pipeline's own
LICENSE and CITATIONS.md under pipelines/<name>/upstream/.

If you use a pipeline through nf-claw, please cite that specific pipeline, the
nf-core framework, and Nextflow:
  - nf-core: Ewels P.A. et al. The nf-core framework for community-curated
    bioinformatics pipelines. Nat Biotechnol 38, 276-278 (2020).
    https://doi.org/10.1038/s41587-020-0439-x
  - Nextflow: Di Tommaso P. et al. Nextflow enables reproducible computational
    workflows. Nat Biotechnol 35, 316-319 (2017).
    https://doi.org/10.1038/nbt.3820

================================================================================
PORTIONS ADAPTED FROM ClawBio (MIT, Copyright (c) Manuel Corpas)
================================================================================
nf-claw adapts some files and its repository structure from ClawBio
(https://clawbio.ai), created by Manuel Corpas and released under the MIT
License. As required by MIT, ClawBio's copyright notice is retained in LICENSE.
Provenance (per the implementation plan):
  - runner/      generic pipeline runtime — consolidated and adapted from
                 ClawBio's per-pipeline nf-core wrapper modules (command builder,
                 executor, pipeline source, schema/params, samplesheet, preflight,
                 outputs, provenance, errors).
  - librarian/   library generation and git-based auto-update tooling —
                 repurposed from ClawBio's scaffolding / catalog / lint scripts.
  - LICENSE, CITATION.cff, and the agent/human docs (CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md,
                 README.md, CONTRIBUTING.md) were kept or rewritten from ClawBio.
  - catalog.*, pipelines/<name>/skill.md and reference.md are generated
                 deterministically from each pipeline's own nextflow_schema.json.

ClawBio: Corpas M. ClawBio: Bioinformatics-Native AI Agent Skill Library.
